For all intents and purposes, the 8 is the default OnePlus device this year.
It’s a serious attempt to break the OnePlus mold, and you can read more about it in Dieter’s full OnePlus 8 Pro review.
The OnePlus 8 hasn’t quite made that same attempt, but it’s still a good phone at a good price.
It’s the OnePlus device to get if you don’t care about the features that OnePlus devices have traditionally been missing.
Like previous OnePlus devices (but unlike the OnePlus 8 Pro), the OnePlus 8 doesn’t support wireless charging.